history.content:
I took 161 without taking 168 or 162 and I thought it was fine. 162 will get you more familiar with debugging in C for the first 161 project, but it's doable nonetheless.

______________

I also took 161 before 168 (but concurrently with 162); I agree that 162 helped a lot with C debugging / lower level concepts at the start of the class, but in the second 'section' of the class, 161 and 168 have a lot of overlap (networking), so I would recommend taking 161 and 168 together if possible. 

______________

168 would definitely help with the networking component in 161.
